718507f-a.title: Manhattan: Central Park West - 90th Street (West)
718507f-a.text:
Central Park West, south from West 90th Street, showing a row of
residential apartment structures facing the western side of Central
Park. Enumerating same in their respective orders are;the Cayuga (No.
296-7), the New Windsor (No. 294-5), a hospital (5 story, No. 292-3),
the New Windsor (No. 294-5), a hospital (5 story, No. 292-3), the
Melbourne (No. 1 West 89th Street), the St. Urban (prominent structure
with corner dome, No. 285), the Progress Club (No. 1 West 88th Street),
the Minnewaska (No. 2 West 88th Street) and the Mohonk (Wo. 275).
Building under construction is the 12 story Hotel Peter Stuyvesant,
No. 2 West 86th Street, at the S.W. corner. Note the eleotric street
oar tracks on the wasterly side of this thoroughfare. These were finally
removed about 1933.
April 1908.
George L. Balgue.
